  "name": "Workflow As A Tool",
  "tool_name": null,
  "description": "Composition demo: an orchestrator agent delegates to two specialist sub-agents wired in as callable tools via control edges — Research (Gemini) gathers the facts, Copy Editor (Claude) polishes the draft, and the manager (GPT-5 mini) decides when to call each. Shows how a self-contained unit of work becomes a tool another agent can invoke, all inside one graph.",
  "tags": [
    "agents",
    "composition",
    "tools",
    "orchestration"
  ],
  "thumbnail": null,
  "thumbnail_url": null,
  "graph": {
    "nodes": [
      {
        "id": "comment-intro",
        "parent_id": null,
        "type": "nodetool.workflows.base_node.Comment",
        "data": {
          "comment": "# 🧩 Workflow As A Tool\n\nThe **orchestrator** (center) is an agent that owns the goal but does none of the specialist work itself. Two other agents are wired to it with **control edges** — the dashed connections into their `__control__` port — which turns each one into a *callable tool*. The orchestrator invokes them by name, passing a task string, and reads back their result.\n\n**Why this shape:** each specialist is a small, self-contained workflow with its own model and system prompt. Exposing it as a tool lets you compose capabilities instead of hard-wiring a fixed pipeline — the manager decides *whether* and *in what order* to call research and editing.\n\n**Cross-workflow version:** a workflow saved with `run_mode: \"tool\"` and a `tool_name` can be called from a *different* graph by adding its name to an agent's Tools list. That needs two saved workflows, so this single-file example uses control edges to show the same idea in one place.\n\n**Try this:** change the topic, or edit the orchestrator's system prompt to call only one specialist."
        },
        "ui_properties": {
          "selected": false,
          "position": {
            "x": 40,
            "y": -260
          },
          "zIndex": 0,
          "width": 520,
          "height": 300,
          "selectable": true
        },
        "dynamic_properties": {},
        "dynamic_outputs": {}
      },
      {
